result.execSummary:
The defendant Alexzander E. Raver was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Substantial Battery-Intend Bodily Harm, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes:
If probation is revoked and a prison term is not ordered, or if probation is discharged or terminated, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of any restitution victims and government entities for outstanding financial obligations.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. Must pay all costs of supervision and court ordered financial obligations during the term of probation. 

The defendant is ORDERED  to report to the Jackson County Jail to submit the required DNA specimen and report for booking. Contact the Jackson County Sheriff's Department at 715-284-5357 to arrange for an appointment.

The defendant shall comply with any treatment, evaluations and/or programming as deemed appropriate by a risk and needs assessment and the probation agent.  Defendant must sign any releases agent deems necessary to verify defendant's compliance with probation conditions. 

Defendant to participate in anger management therapy and follow through with recommendations deemed appropriate by agent.

Defendant must undergo a domestic violence assessment and follow through with any recommendations deemed appropriate by agent.

4 Days jail credit if Revoked.
Defendant shall have no contact, directly or indirectly, either personally, by mail, telephone or through any other person, with any of the following individual:  Victim
May be eligible for expungement if successfully discharges from probation.

1:54 PM Defendant Alexzander E. Raver in court.  Attorney Marsolek and Jensen in court for State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Carly June Sebion in court for Alexzander E. Raver. State in compliance with victim rights issues. Pleads No Contest to Count 1. all other charges DRI.
 Court reviewed the elements and potential penalties of the charge the defendant plead to.  He understood.   Court reviewed the plea questionnaire, constitutional rights and elements with the defendant. Felony warnings given.  He understood. Defense stipulated that there is a factual basis for the plea.   Court found that the defendant freely, voluntarily, knowingly and intelligently entered his plea and waived his constitutional rights.  Court found that a factual basis exists for the plea.  Found guilty of Substantial Battery-Intend Bodily Harm contrary to 940.19(2). Defendant exercised his right to allocution. 

Joint recommendation: Sentence withheld,  2 years probation, Domestic Violence Evaluation and programming, Risks/Needs Assessment and programming ordered by Agent. . No contact w/Victim 1, if successfully completes probation, allow expunction. 

Court adopts the joint recommendation: Sentence withheld, 2 years probation. Participate in any Domestic Violence Evaluation and programming, Risks/Needs Assessment and programming ordered by Agent. Participate in anger management therapy. No contact w/Victim, if successfully completes probation without violations, all fees paid, court finds successfully rehabilitated, may be allowed to expunge. Pay costs through probation. 

The defendant is ORDERED  to report to the Jackson County Jail to submit the required DNA specimen and report for booking. Contact the Jackson County Sheriff's Department at 715-284-5357 to arrange for an appointment.  4 days sentence credit, if later revoked.
